USAGE:

Run "sudo vjoy.py --sensitivity [your TF2 sensitivity]".

To use this script, you need to install evdev (http://gvalkov.github.com/python-evdev/):
	pip install evdev
Evdev requires python-dev

Usage: sudo vjoy.py [-h] [-d DEVICE] --sensitivity SENSITIVITY
                            [--adjustment ADJUSTMENT] [--fps FPS]
                            [--joy_yawsensitivity JOY_YAWSENSITIVITY]
                            [--cl_yawspeed CL_YAWSPEED] [--m_yaw M_YAW]

Maps keyboard inputs to joystick inputs.

Required arguments:
  --sensitivity SENSITIVITY, -s SENSITIVITY
                        sensitivity from TF2.

Optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -k DEVICE, --keyboard DEVICE
                        Keyboard device. By default, the script attempts to
                        find the keyboard in /dev/input/event*.
  -m DEVICE, --mouse DEVICE
                        Mouse device. By default, the script attempts to find
                        the mouse in /dev/input/event*.
  --adjustment ADJUSTMENT, -a ADJUSTMENT
                        Sensitivity adjustment factor.
  --fps FPS             Framerate of script (how often it updates the
                        joystick).
  --joy_yawsensitivity JOY_YAWSENSITIVITY
                        joy_yawsensitivity from TF2.
  --cl_yawspeed CL_YAWSPEED
                        cl_yawspeed from TF2.
  --m_yaw M_YAW         m_yaw from TF2.

